>>Whats the secret for removing stubborn push rod
tubes?<<

--- Andrew Burczyk <Andrew.Burczyk(-at-)monarch.net>
 replied:
>>To keep from damaging the pushrod tube I put a
 small hose clamp around it and tighten it down, then
grab the clamp with a vice grip<<

Andrew, this worked GREAT!! I put the hose clamps
around the push rod tubes and tightened them down,
then I grabbed the "tail" of the hose clamp strap with
the vice grip and was able to get enough leverage to
pull that dog right out!! Thanks for the help!!  

